  "prompt": "Who is Amartya Sen?",
  "response": "Amartya Sen is an Indian economist and philosopher, born on November 3, 1933, in Santiniketan, India. He is renowned for his contributions to welfare economics, social choice theory, and development economics. Sen's work has emphasized the importance of individual capabilities and well-being, advocating for a broader understanding of poverty that goes beyond mere income measurement.\n\nHe is best known for his capability approach, which assesses individuals' well-being based on their ability to achieve valuable functionings and the freedoms they possess to pursue various life paths. Sen's influential books include \"Development as Freedom\" and \"The Idea of Justice.\" \n\nIn 1998, he was awarded the Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences for his contributions to welfare economics, particularly in analyzing the causes of famine and poverty. Throughout his career, Sen has also been involved in policy-making and has held various academic positions, including at Harvard University and the London School of Economics. His work has had a significant impact on development policy and economic theory, making him one of the leading intellectual figures of his time.",
